article.description: Keith Braxton had 18 points and 10 rebounds to carry St. Francis (Pa.) to a 77-69 win over Lehigh on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Braxton leads St. Francis (Pa.) over Lehigh 77-69
article.linkText: Braxton leads St. Francis (Pa.) over Lehigh 77-69
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Keith Braxton had 18 points and 10 rebounds to carry St. Francis (Pa.) to a 77-69 win over Lehigh on Wednesday night. Braxton converted all 10 of his free-throw attempts. He added nine assists. Myles Thompson had 12 points for St. Francis (Pa.) (4-4). Jordan Cohen had 22 points for the Mountain Hawks (3-6), whose losing streak stretched to four games. James Karnik added 18 points and 13 rebounds. Reed Fenton had 13 points. St. Francis (Pa.) matches up against Maryland-Baltimore County on the road on Saturday. Lehigh faces Yale at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
